I had been meaning to come back and post details of what we found out with the
patch... It broke the functionality of the welcome screen and had to be
modified. As you say, there is some weird dependency on that pointer being
incorrect. What we went with in the end was

    public void add(LayoutPart child) {
        children.add(child);
        if(!(child.getContainer() instanceof ContainerPlaceholder))
            child.setContainer(this);
        showPart(child, null);
    }

    /**
     * Add a part at a particular position
     */
    protected void add(LayoutPart newChild, Object cookie) {
        children.add(newChild);
        if(!(newChild.getContainer() instanceof ContainerPlaceholder))
            newChild.setContainer(this);
        showPart(newChild, cookie);
    }

We did a full set of tests for our plugins and didn't find any problems after
that change. Good luck with it!
